        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 6:59PM EDT until July 8 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>SVROKX

The National Weather Service in Upton NY has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Queens County in southeastern New York...
Richmond County in southeastern New York...
Kings County in southeastern New York...

* Until 800 PM EDT.

* At 658 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Sayreville,
or near Perth Amboy, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Huguenot and Tottenville around 705 PM EDT.
Oakwood around 710 PM EDT.
Todt Hill around 715 PM EDT.
The Verrazano Narrows Bridge and Bay Ridge around 720 PM EDT.
Coney Island and Sheepshead Bay around 725 PM EDT.
Flatbush and Crown Heights around 730 PM EDT.
Canarsie and Howard Beach around 735 PM EDT.
Ozone Park around 740 PM EDT.
Forest Hills around 745 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
